[ti:Ma rose éternelle]
[lang:en]
[length:03:46.80]
[re:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0n903tvXZ0I]

[00:04.28] Beneath the pale moon of Montmartre,
[00:12.72] the years were falling like leaves too light.
[00:18.60] My heart kept a closed garden, without a voice.
[00:24.24] Every evening, the wind scattered what little fever remained,
[00:29.12] and the world forgot its sweetness of former days.
[00:33.35]
[00:35.84] Then your hands gathered my solitude,
[00:40.80] and time slipped off its heavy cloak.
[00:47.44] A single rose bloomed within my chest,
[00:52.36] and the night began to believe in day again.
[00:57.04] You are my eternal rose,
[01:02.64] the one that watches over the fire of my nights.
[01:08.44] Even when the wind rises and wounds me,
[01:13.56] my life regains its colour close to you.
[01:19.40] You are my eternal rose,
[01:25.08] the one that yields nothing to winter.
[01:30.80] In the living velvet of your petals,
[01:35.52] I find the sun again upon the earth.
[01:41.53] The winters came, then withdrew without a sound,
[01:47.64] and your flower kept its summer fragrance.
[01:52.60] The streetlamps of Paris tremble for us in the mist,
[01:57.92] and every paving stone holds your name like a secret.
[02:04.08] I no longer fear time in its graceless course,
[02:09.32] for in your arms, every second learns to last.
[02:15.72] You turn my tears into pearls of dew,
[02:20.56] and my heart begins again with the breath of a future.
[02:26.44] Even if tomorrow the roses of the world should fade,
[02:32.20] even if life should lead us astray for a moment,
[02:37.68] one single reflection of you in the mist of a window
[02:43.28] is enough to give the evening back its former sweetness.
[02:48.56] You are my eternal rose,
[02:54.16] the one that watches over the fire of my nights.
[02:59.92] Even when the wind rises and wounds me,
[03:04.92] my life regains its colour close to you.
[03:10.76] You are my eternal rose,
[03:15.44] the one that yields nothing to winter.
[03:22.56] And I am reborn in silence within your velvet shadow,
[03:30.84] with you, for eternity.
[03:40.80]
